00:32:35.190 --> 00:32:36.810
where you're
basically just working

00:32:36.810 --> 00:32:41.780
with textures and
spheres with gradients.

00:32:41.780 --> 00:32:44.000
And it was Photoshop.

00:32:44.000 --> 00:32:47.350
And honestly, Photoshop I
work in more than Illustrator.

00:32:47.350 --> 00:32:50.040
I do so much in Photoshop.

00:32:50.040 --> 00:32:52.320
[FF] My experience
is that when I

00:32:52.320 --> 00:32:57.870
have to make an image in
order to explain the science,

00:32:57.870 --> 00:33:03.380
the process of making the image
clarifies the science for me.

00:33:03.380 --> 00:33:04.500
[CD] Definitely.

00:33:04.500 --> 00:33:07.670
Somebody said to me once,
when they asked what I did,

00:33:07.670 --> 00:33:09.750
and I said I illustrate
the MIT homepage,

00:33:09.750 --> 00:33:12.440
